50.body:
Shamelessly plundered from this course . It's meant to be used for driver modules. Inserts a module and creates an associated file in /dev #!/bin/sh
# insdev <module> [params]
module=$1
shift
/sbin/insmod ./$module.ko $* || exit 1
rm -f /dev/$module
major=$(awk "\$2==\"$module\" {print \$1}" /proc/devices)
mknod /dev/$module c $major 0
chmod 666 /dev/$module
50.title: insdev

52.body:
Shamelessly plundered from this course . It's meant to be used for driver modules. Removes a module but also deletes the associated file in /dev #!/bin/sh
# rmdev <module>
module=$1
/sbin/rmmod $module || exit 1
rm -f /dev/$module
